SIMPLE: insociable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insociable
<hw>In*so"cia*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insociabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>insociable</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Sociable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Incapable of being associated, joined, or
connected.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lime and wood are <qex>insociable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir H.
Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not sociable or companionable; disinclined to social
intercourse or conversation; unsociable; taciturn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This austere <qex>insociable</qex> life.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insociably</ent>⟦br⟧
